  "slug": "chicken-and-ham-pie",
  "title": "Chicken and Ham Pie",
  "subtitle": "A deep-filled shortcrust pie with a creamy leek sauce and tender pulled chicken",
  "excerpt": "Chicken and ham pie is the definitive British weekend pie: shortcrust pastry enclosing pulled roast chicken, flaked ham, leeks, and a cream sauce. It is best made with leftover roast chicken and a proper ham joint, but works equally well with poached thighs and cooked gammon.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British savoury pie. Jane Grigson, English Food (1974): raised pie tradition. Delia Smith, Complete Cookery Course (1978): chicken pie with cream sauce. Cross-referenced across multiple period sources.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A proper chicken and ham pie has a thick shortcrust pastry case, a filling that is distinctly saucy rather than dry, and a top crust that goes in golden and crisp. The sauce is made from the poaching liquid if you cook the chicken from scratch, or from a good chicken stock if you are using leftovers. Either way, the sauce must be slightly over-seasoned at the making stage because the pastry will absorb some of the salt during baking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The pastry base is not ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "blind baked",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp5q86lz0000i0v4jdo0db27"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " because the filling is already cooked; the pie needs only 50-55 minutes to heat through and colour the crust. An ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "egg wash",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp73tbq90000wov4k6oi7wjo"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " on the lid before baking is not optional: it is what turns the top crust from pale and dull to the golden-brown that a pie deserves.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
